Due to Governor Murphy's executive order today further reducing the capacity of indoor gatherings to a maximum of 25 people, we are postponing tonight's board meeting. It will now be held via Zoom on Friday, August 7th at 6:00 PM. The link to the meeting will be posted on our website.

You can access this meeting at this link: https://zoom.us/j/93090544769?pwd=aDAxbnBxNVJKUDlsbXpUck5DTzR2QT09

Meeting ID: 930 9054 4769
Passcode: g6C8kJ
We apologize for this unexpected inconvenience to you and your families, but we want to make sure as many people as possible can participate in this important meeting.

post_text:
August 3rd Board Meeting

Monday night's meeting is open for attendance to members of the general public. The live stream link is available for the meeting for those that are unable to attend due to the limited capacity in the OMS all-purpose room as mandated by social distancing requirements. Please note all of those in attendance must wear masks, be temperature screened prior to entrance, and maintain 6 ft. social distancing requirements.

The Board of Education meeting that will take place at 6 PM on August 3rd will be livestreamed on YouTube. The meeting can be watched live by clicking this link: https://youtu.be/eGFtx4W6T8k.

Please use this link to leave a comment or question to be addressed at a board meeting: https://forms.gle/jsNtGBWjURT2duG28. People who would like to address the board or ask a question can do so through the end of the public comment period. All questions and comments will be read to the board.

Statement Regarding Main Office Hours

Dear Parents/Guardians,

The Tabernacle School District will be closed until Monday, April 20. At this time, the OMS Main Office will be open on Mondays from 9:00 am - 12:00 pm if you need to come to school for anything. This is subject to change. If you need to call TES or OMS for any reason, please call 609-268-0153 x1001. This is for both schools. If you need to call Mrs. Latini, OMS school nurse, please call 609-251-7309. If you need to call Mrs. Wisniewski, TES school nurse, please call 609-251-8218. Please stay well.

post_text:
Comcast is offering two free months of Internet services to low-income customers. Customers are eligible to receive Internet Essentials if they are eligible for public assistance programs such as the National School Lunch program, Medicaid or SNAP and live in a Comcast service area.

New customers will be sent a free self-install kit that includes a cable modem with a WiFi router. There will be no term contract or credit check and no shipping fee. To sign up for the service, visit the Internet Essentials website or call 1-855-846-8376 for English speakers and 1-855-765-6995 for Spanish.

It’s the most wonderful time of the year! Please join us as we welcome in the holiday season at the HSA’s Family Holiday Palooza next Friday, November 22nd! So many fun activities for our Tabernacle families! The evening begins at 5:30 pm with a complimentary dinner (generously provided by the Tabernacle Municipal Alliance). Dinner will be provided until we run out! Thank you Municipal Alliance!!!! The rest of the holiday fun begins at 6:00 pm. As always we will have our Scholastic Book Fair, Cake Walk, Visits with Santa, movie, and Tabernacle Scout tables. There will be kids holiday games in the gym, family board games in the DEN and A & B Color Creations will also be there for face painting and sand art! NEW THIS YEAR- amazing raffle baskets!!!!! So many wonderful donations from families and businesses in our community. Thank you all!!! Raffle tickets will be for sale that night for $1 per ticket or $20 for 25 tickets! Please see the flyer below for more event info. and hope to see you at the Palooza! ⛄️🎅🎄

The Toshiba of America Foundation has awarded the Education Foundation of Tabernacle Township a $3,800 grant for Olson Middle School’s “The Impact of Erosion on a Bioswale” project.

Additionally, the Education Foundation of Tabernacle Township has received a $6,500 grant from the Carolyn Jane Scott Charitable Trust to bring back woodworking to students via a “Construction Kids” project.

September 17, 2019 at 9:02 AM ·

The Toshiba of America Foundation has awarded the Education Foundation of Tabernacle Township a $3,800 grant for Olson Middle School’s “The Impact of Erosion on a Bioswale” project.

Additionally, the Education Foundation of Tabernacle Township has received a $6,500 grant from the Carolyn Jane Scott Charitable Trust to bring back woodworking to students via a “Construction Kids” project.

August 25, 2019 at 11:00 AM ·

With the start of school just around the corner, it’s time to start thinking about our 2019-2020 fundraising efforts! Box Tops is a simple way to earn funds for our students, classrooms and schools! Did you know our lifetime school earnings through Box Tops totals $22,533? That’s amazing!!!! Please see below for information on the new digital format. Earning will be easier than ever by just downloading the Box Tops app to your phone and scanning receipts. While clipped boxed tops are being phased out, you can still clip them and send into school until the expiration date has expired. Thanks in advance for your support!!!

Also, if you shop at Shop Rite, please link your price plus card to Tabernacle Schools. Click on the link below to register you Shop Rite Plus Card #, choose Tabernacle Elementary School and start automatically turning your Box Tops purchases into cash for our schools every time you shop!

https://www.shopriteformyschool.com/

June 7, 2019 at 11:43 AM ·

It’s time to order your child’s school supplies for the 2019-2020 school year! We know it’s hard to think about next year already but don’t miss out on this amazingly easy service where you purchase your child’s supply kit online and they will be waiting at school on their first day in September. Simply follow the link below, choose TES or OMS and choose your child’s grade in the fall. It’s so simple and eliminates us parents needing to run around in August gathering everything on the list. There are even backpacks, lunch boxes and water bottles available for purchase. The deadline for ordering is June 30th.

https://www.1stdayschoolsupplies.com/list.php?school_zip=08088

post_text: Mayor Barton, Dr. Birnbohm, Dr. Jones, Mrs. Cutts, Mrs. Egan, and Mr. Robbins attended a joint meeting in Trenton today, consisting of other superintendents, educators, leaders from NJEA, NJASBO, NJPTA, NJSBA, NJASA, NJPSA, and other organizations, who are all teaming together to fight against state school aid cuts. We will continue to fight for our children, staff, and community as these state aid cuts need to stop!!!
